New Adventures in Hi-Fi is the tenth studio album by the American 
alternative rock band R.E.M. It was their fifth major label release 
for Warner Bros. Records, released on September 9, 1996, in Europe 
and Australia and the following day in the United States. 
New Adventures in Hi-Fi was the last album recorded with founding 
member Bill Berry (who left the band amicably the following year) 
original manager Jefferson Holt, and long-time producer Scott Litt.
